title: Microneedle patches for flu vaccination prove successful in first human clinical trial
description: Researchers believe a new self-administered, painless vaccine skin patch containing microscopic needles could significantly increase the number of people who get vaccinated for the flu. Read full story: http://www.rh.gatech.edu/features/microneedle-patches-flu-vaccination-prove-successful-first-human-clinical-trial
